cardinfo.CI: Syzygium - Brush Cherry Tree/Brush Cherry Tree - Canopy.jpg

V: The leaves are opposite, simple, lanceolate from 4–8 cm long. Flowers are white and in clusters. The dark pink to red fruits are edible.[3] This species is commonly confused with Magenta Cherry and the Blue Lilly Pilly. However, the Brush Cherry has a paler trunk.
